[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring reflection and instantiation**\n\nI’m considering whether Native can allow Class.newInstance if the class lacks a nullary constructor. Oh, to instantiate reflectively, the constructor must be registered with invoke metadata. If there’s a Class constant with a public constructor, it might be \"unsafeAllocated,\" but that’s not everything. There’s no current test covering this in native, so I think we could add a reflection config for BasicDBObject and potentially keep it simple. We might only need to create a Java file for this.\n\n**Exploring database integration**\n\nI’m considering using a public API, but direct creation might feel artificial. I want to ensure there's high-coverage integration. I think the DBObjectCodec could be useful, especially for decoding BSON with a callback. But hmm, maybe using BasicDBObject.parse would feel more natural? I'll have to search for more specifics to see which approach fits best and how I can effectively manage those callbacks.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_09b8df3d7161eb8e0169f12b795e6481a2808bd076a5141740\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8SuFSgMVm8ysUFXWk-FzN94B6hKBH7yyXVBFJ4k8Sy9HQtAOChG-k3q-IldLPOnR6yHy7h9Mn4UeF613HJYXutj7YMatfYftoEy6sEZxMm4XbI7GONtDaF2GNSKt2dTg9zfnV8MQu6fqpsN0RVsatWKw7NIw0i7qgdWHWKcUfo1CavV7YVJNywAIt-W3LIUlMe54gTDOI00Y_vTgwRefVCJ5o7QiIoJ1fb07YbdYGBHT_ZJjpcyQpH-jAoWKdtAMFnaKLLOicR6tFJSqtBUqtuAJJRR-zrwHXSn7864QcF4uFJPiEzF2UZJYs38R2YH0mDwwGsOlxsjFU_6Xf27sab7PWNbrBJVKxO6dbuRDFLkKLeeoO1MP8F9YlGg_oxs1RrkN5Pdz8Sm0vsml8a55j_K2G505EaaiT3SCg8kNvMDzTJxj2A1ObgieV3NzZ8XAYhvoPV36iF2QCE7iSEQy5heVQhXFc52E1pJrDXia_uadX1KO7Yjo_mMpZqMdskaTePmY1i0BCz8-HV1BXCCEWk8w-dsu8NahropKGyOuefEkqFyfdQWRHedhdS5eN3pczEYVcBrI5scICpTRqR80DNnWpd9d2j-aUMUO5_zoab45CDN8Zi0Y31g3V6gialIrHSMcUucJB090QRe9rMlr_ZP710QSNsN-1lP_2OSroPvUTufq7iWT605ttYi_xwIxtorApLtP65QyHH4rqxYcKx5EciKmU_37QfJaH2F3-AldFdJFZf